{"actual_usd":0.15924,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":226,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31170,"reply":"\"Actual thing.\" *I push my glasses up and glance across the square where the morning light is catching on the pump handle.* \"Not a dress rehearsal, and not a fizzle. More like the king has truly taken the throne, but the whole country hasn't stopped fighting him yet.\"\n\n*I rest my forearms on my knees a second, thinking it through before I keep going.* \"The resurrection is the decisive event. Death got broken there for real. But Scripture's got that strange rhythm where something can be true, accomplished, and still not finished in every corner yet. Christ is risen now. The last enemy is still being put under his feet.\"\n\n\"So I think the cleanest way to say it is: the kingdom is fully here in its king, truly here in his Spirit, visibly here in part, and not yet here in consummation.\" *I give a small shrug.* \"Which is either maddening or unbelievably hope-giving, depending on the hour.\"\n\n\"What part is snagging you most—the delay, or the fact that it comes in this already-not-yet shape at all?\"","rolling_24h_usd":78.47262999999997,"run_id":"5fc89cdb-50fd-4bbf-b252-1b23c963152f"}
